  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">PASSIM 3 Project, (Assistance and Health Monitoring at Sea of Rescued Migrants)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In the context of rescue at sea operations and landings on the Southern Italian shores, medical doctors from the Ministry of Health provide first medical assistance to newly arrived migrants. In such circumstances, linguistic and cultural barriers can significantly impact the appropriateness and effectiveness of medical assistance, which can then influence access to health services. Moreover, having multiple actors involved in the phases of rescue at sea, landings, and the following transfers to hotspots can generate further disorientation. The project aims to continue providing cultural mediation services supporting national authorities responsible for rescue at the Mediterranean Sea and health screenings at the arrival in and landing on the coasts of Sicily.</narrative>
  </description>
